[30;1m20 | [0m[35m    Adapters provide an interface to resources, so they can be queried via[0m
[30;1m21 | [0m[35m    SQL. An adapter instance represents a virtual table, and the adapter is[0m
[30;1m22 | [0m[35m    responsible for fetching data and metadata from the resource, and[0m
[30;1m23 | [0m[35m    possibly insert, delete, or update rows.[0m
[30;1m24 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m25 | [0m[35m    In order to find an adapter responsible for a given table name, adapters[0m
[30;1m26 | [0m[35m    need to be registered under the "shillelagh.adapter" entry point, eg::[0m
